1. Install the Python  

python.org

to check the version

>> python --version (windows)
>> python3 --version

->type python in cmd or bash to enter into the shell , (python3 for MAC)
-> to come out <exit()>

2.Install Editors (SUBLIME , VSCODE )

3. Anacoda Juypter notebook
 -> create a practise working directory (mkdir)
 -> change the path to that diretory (cd /path)
 -> install the jupyter by this command <conda install jupyter notebook>

 -> to open the jupyter notebook type <jupyter notebook> in cmd or bash
 ->it will be opened in default browser.
-> to stop : CNTRL+D or C


4. Clone the GitHUB

